&lt;p style="margin-bottom: 15px; font-style: italic;"&gt;Former F.B.I. director James Comey has been hauled into federal court over a photograph of seashells arranged in the sand, an image the Justice Department has deemed a “serious threat” to the president.

Seashells.

One imagines the Founders, having just finished debating the separation of powers, pausing to ask: “But what if someone arranges the exoskeletons of dead mollusks in a vaguely suggestive manner?”&lt;/p&gt;
